<br>
With a couple <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/newspells.html?source=Test&amp;date=2004-08-17%2020:54:08">test</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/newspells.html?source=Test&amp;date=2004-08-17%2018:14:04">patches</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> from today, the first info that I have seen about any OoW AAs and/or skills showed up on test.  Looks like stuff for every class, but the stuff that looked of interest to us was:<br>
<br>
Master of Disguise - This ability lends persistence to your illusionary disguises, causing them to last until you die or manually remove them. (rogue and bard I assume)<br>
<br>
Brewing Mastery - This ability reduces the chance of failing brewing combinations by 10, 25, and 50 percent.<br>
<br>
Expansive Mind - This ability raises the maximum that your mana regeneration can be increased with items by 5 points per rank.<br>
<br>
Fortified Bellowing - This ability allows you to bellow with a force that causes physical harm to your enemies as well as potentially interfering with spell casting. This upgraded ability does more damage and increases the maximum level of NPC that can be stunned by your bellows.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=5825&amp;source=Test">Fortified Bellowing I</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=5826&amp;source=Test">Fortified Bellowing II</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=5827&amp;source=Test">Fortified Bellowing III</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
